title: For Sale:  "EBS-47" AK Bump Fire Stock
postcontent:
I have an AK bump fire stock (sized for Eastern Bloc tang length) that a buddy of mine made out of an ATI Dragunov style AK thumbhole stock. He sells them for $225 apiece, but I am only looking for $150 for mine.

The bump fire stock allows the shooter to safely and effectively bump fire his AK pattern rifle while it's shouldered, allowing him or her to actually aim and not have to hold it in an awkward position. The stock is affixed to the tang but cut so that it moves back and forth with a tab for the trigger finger so the recoil of the gun works the trigger. These are 100% legal and their AR-15 (branded Slide Fire) counterparts come with a letter from the ATF saying as much, since each shot is still an individual pull of the trigger!

The linked video is me firing my WASR-10 with the bump fire stock pictured in this ad.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-JQyuLsPSM

Cash only please, no trades.

postcontent:
5.56 55gr Tracer Rounds

These are US Military surplus rounds manufactured at the Lake City Munitions Plant in 1980 (Headstamp LC-80) and stored in sealed ammo cans. The M196 tracer cartridge (55-grain bullet) is a training round for 5.56mm NATO weapons. It has a red tip and is designed to trace out to 500 yards. This ammo is not reloaded and has never been used, but tracer elements do expire over time, and I cannot guarantee the tracing effects of these rounds. However, the ballistics are not affected and these are great 5.56 rounds for your AR 15.

The package comes with two (2) shoulder strap bandoliers loaded with 7 boxes in pouches. Each box contains two (2) stripper clips with 10 rounds each for a total of 280 rounds.

These are a great alternative to high priced AR 15 ammo.
